  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil&nbsp;a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Heat a pot with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>ground</strong>&nbsp;<strong>cinnamon</strong> and<strong> basmati rice</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and stir for 1 min or until the rice is coated in oil and spice&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/510_step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/510_step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/510_step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/510_step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/510_step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 350ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[750ml]</span><strong>&nbsp;cold water</strong>&nbsp;to the <strong>rice</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, place the <strong>coconut cream sachet<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span>&nbsp;</strong>in a mug and cover with <strong>boiled water</strong> (this softens the naturally hard cream)&nbsp;and set aside</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Lato; font-size: 15px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/510_step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/510_step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/510_step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/510_step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/510_step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of&nbsp;<strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>onion</strong> with a big pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 3-5 min or until softened and glossy</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/510_step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/510_step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/510_step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/510_step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/510_step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, reduce the<strong> onion</strong>&nbsp;to medium-low, add the <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>curry powder</strong> and cook for a further 5 min or until they're caramelised</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, drain the <strong>king prawns</strong> and pat them dry with kitchen paper</p>\r\n<p>Combine&nbsp;the <strong>softened coconut cream</strong> and 150ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [250ml]</span>&nbsp;<strong>boiled water </strong>- this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/510_step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/510_step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/510_step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/510_step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/510_step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>king prawns</strong> to the caramelised<strong> onions</strong>, increase the heat to medium and cook for 1 min or until the prawns are pink and opaque</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/510_step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/510_step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/510_step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/510_step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/510_step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>coconut stock</strong> and <strong>fish sauce</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until reduced to a curry-like consistency</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, finely chop the<strong> coriander</strong>, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/510_step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
